&rolestep.sgm;
Edit the /etc/cron.d/cron.deny file and add user names, one user per line. Include users who will be denied access to the crontab commands.daemon bin smtp nuucp listen nobody noaccess username1 username2 username3 . . .
Verify that the /etc/cron.d/cron.deny file contains the new entries.# cat /etc/cron.d/cron.deny daemon bin nuucp listen nobody noaccess
